The Python code first imports the required libraries from NLTK and downloads necessary datasets such as punkt, stopwords, and wordnet. Two paragraphs containing punctuation marks are stored as input text. The program then removes punctuation using Python’s string module and converts the text into tokens using word tokenization. After tokenization, stop words such as is, the, and, of are removed to keep only meaningful words. Next, stemming is applied using the Porter Stemmer to reduce words to their root form. Finally, lemmatization is performed using the WordNet Lemmatizer to convert words into their dictionary base form. The processed results of each step are printed as output.
